  "prompt": "Why should I tip my server?",
  "response": "Tipping your server is a way to show appreciation for the service provided during your dining experience. Here are some reasons why tipping is considered important:\n\n1. **Supplementing Income**: In many places, servers rely on tips to supplement their income, as their base wages are often lower than the standard minimum wage.\n\n2. **Recognizing Service**: Tipping is a direct way to reward good service. If your server has been attentive, polite, and helpful, tipping acknowledges their effort and encourages continued good service.\n\n3. **Cultural Norms**: In countries like the United States, tipping is a well-established social convention. While this may vary between countries, in places where tipping is customary, it is generally expected as part of the dining cost.\n\n4. **Encouragement**: Tips can motivate servers to provide exceptional service, create a friendly dining environment, and go beyond the basic requirements of their job.\n\n5. **Shared Tips**: Servers often share their tips with other staff members, such as cooks, bussers, and bartenders, who contribute to your dining experience but don't interact directly with customers.\n\n6. **Acknowledging Hard Work**: Serving can be a physically and emotionally demanding job. Tipping is a way of recognizing and valuing this hard work.\n\nWhile tipping is generally seen as essential in some cultures, it can vary globally, and it's important to be aware of local customs and expectations when dining out in different countries.",
